{"editorCode":";The procedure \"riddle\" constructs two broken line segments, whose heights depend on the polynomials of the variable x as below: \n\n;For the black one, it's the \n;(2x^2-5x-3)(x+1) and\n;for the red one it's the\n;2x^3-3x^2-ax-3.\n\n;Can you find the right value for the parameter a in order for the lines to be of the same height (for any value of the variable x)? \n;For further instructions, click on the papyrus button.\n\n\nTO polynomial1 :x\nfd (2*:x*:x - 5*:x - 3)*(:x + 1)\nlt 90 fd 20\nend\n\nclean\npolynomial1 4\n\n\nto polynomial2 :x :a\nfd 2*:x*:x*:x - 3*:x*:x - :a*:x - 3\nrt 90 fd 20\nend\n\nclean\npolynomial2 4 6\n\n\nto riddle :x :a\npolynomial1 :x\npu home pd\nsetpencolor [255 0 0]\npolynomial2 :x :a\nsetpencolor [0 0 0]\nend\n\nclean\nriddle 4 6\n\n\n\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"                              ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::\n\n                              Find the secret number\n                              ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::\n\nINTRODUCTION\n----------------\nEach one of the procedures \"polynomial1\" and \"polynomial2\" constructs a broken line that consists of two line segments, a vertical and a horizontal one. \n\nThe vertical segment constructed by the \"polynomial1\" has length equal to (2x^2-5x-3)(x+1), \nwhile the vertical segment constructed by the \"polynomial1\" has length equal to 2x^3-3x^2-ax-3.\n\nThe procedure \"riddle\" constructs both of the broken lines at the same time, coloring the second one with red color. \n\n\n\nTASK\n--------------------------\n Run the command \"riddle 4 6\" and enable the variation tool (by clicking on the avatar's trace). \nSet the limit values of the variable t from -4 to 5 and the step value to 0.5. \n\n1)  Set the x value to x=4 and try to find the right value for the parameter a in order for the black and the red lines to be of the same height (and the horizontal segments to be aligned). \n2)  Repeat the same for different values of the variable x (positive, negative or 0) \n3) Try to find a value of the parameter a for which the two horizontal segments are always aligned, for any value of the variable x. Can you justify your observation? \n\n\n\nTIP\n-----------------\n3) The requested value for the parameter a can be found when the values of the two polynomials are equal, that is when:\n    \n                  (2x^2-5x-3)(x+1)=2x^3-3x^2-ax-3\n\n\n\n\n\n","sliders":{},"objects":[]}